Desktop To Cloud (D2C)
------------------------------

Required libraries:
wxPython
http://wiki.wxpython.org/InstallingOnUbuntuOrDebian

mockito-python
http://code.google.com/p/mockito-python/
easy_install mockito

Required tools:
VirtualBox
Installation instructions for Ubuntu 10:
http://www.techienote.com/2010/10/installing-virtualbox-on-ubuntu-10-10.html
Note: instead of installing package viturtualbox-3.2, I installed virtualbox-ose.
The only required executable from this package is VirtualBoxManage.

After installing this in a development VirtualBox VM, I got errors during the boot process about 
being unable to mount the shared host folder due to an invalid vmboxsf.ko module. This was fixed by
running insmod on the module. See following for more details:
http://forums.virtualbox.org/viewtopic.php?f=3&t=33413

boto - Python library wrapping AWS web service
http://code.google.com/p/boto/
Currently developing against version 2.0 Beta 4


EC2 AMI Tools
http://s3.amazonaws.com/ec2-downloads/ec2-ami-tools.zip
Tools for bundling and uploading AMIs. Recommended installation directory is /opt/EC2TOOLS.

EC2 API Tools
http://s3.amazonaws.com/ec2-downloads/ec2-api-tools.zip

EC2 AMI Tools dependencies:
        - curl
        - gzip
        - mkfifo
        - openssl
        - rsync
        - Ruby 1.8.2 or later
			- Might need to explicitly install libopenssl-ruby
        - tee
        
 guestfish and python-guestfs
 http://libguestfs.org/download/binaries/debian-packages/
